{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-a76bea130108",
  "content": "## CLI Surface (D48)\n\n### New Subcommand Group\n\n```\ncorvia workspace create <name>     Scaffold a new workspace\n    --repo <url>                   Add a repo (repeatable)\n    --template <url|path>          Scaffold from a template workspace\n    --local <name>=<path>          Set local override for a repo\n\ncorvia workspace init              Initialize workspace in current directory\n                                   (reads existing corvia.toml, clones missing repos, sets up .corvia/)\n\ncorvia workspace status            Show repos, ingest state, knowledge counts per namespace\n\ncorvia workspace add <url>         Add a repo to the workspace\n    --name <name>                  Override repo name (default: derived from URL)\n    --namespace <ns>               Override namespace (default: same as name)\n    --local <path>                 Set local path override\n\ncorvia workspace remove <name>     Remove a repo from workspace config\n    --purge                        Also delete cloned repo + its knowledge entries\n\ncorvia workspace ingest            Ingest all workspace repos\n    --fresh                        Re-ingest from scratch (discard existing knowledge)\n    --repo <name>                  Only ingest this specific repo\n```\n\n\n### Existing Command Adaptation\n\n- `corvia ingest` (no path) in a workspace → equivalent to `corvia workspace ingest`\n- `corvia search` → results include namespace (repo origin) in output\n- `corvia status` → shows workspace-level info when in a workspace\n- `corvia init` → if `corvia.toml` with `[workspace]` exists, behaves as `corvia workspace init`\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-01-m2.1-workspace-devcontainer-design.md",
